1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:10,010


2
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:37,030
In the Name of Blossom

3
00:01:37,030 --> 00:01:39,960
 

4
00:02:03,940 --> 00:02:06,659
What's wrong, Mu Dan? Did you cut your hand?

5
00:02:06,659 --> 00:02:08,400
Let me see.

6
00:02:08,400 --> 00:02:11,420
It's okay. It will be fine soon.

7
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:19,260
Is this an auspicious cloud
you're carving? It's so intricate.

8
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:22,740
It needs a bit more refining.

9
00:02:22,740 --> 00:02:25,719
Once it's done, this auspicious cloud

10
00:02:25,719 --> 00:02:29,900
can be printed
on the sachets for gifts, symbolizing good luck.

11
00:02:30,939 --> 00:02:34,560
I never knew you could carve stamps.

12
00:02:36,159 --> 00:02:38,360
My mother taught me.

13
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:45,639
Mu Dan, you have turned
the Fragrance Garden into a riot of color.

14
00:02:45,639 --> 00:02:50,379
Your mother would be very proud of you.

15
00:02:52,520 --> 00:02:58,700
If I can't personally take revenge on the enemy,
how can I live up to my mother's expectations?

16
00:03:01,960 --> 00:03:05,059
Jiang Chang Yang came today looking for you.

17
00:03:05,059 --> 00:03:09,759
Liu Lang sent him away,
saying that you didn't feel like seeing guests.

18
00:03:13,520 --> 00:03:18,440
I thought that after spending so much time together,

19
00:03:18,440 --> 00:03:21,060
I understood him well enough.

20
00:03:23,080 --> 00:03:25,779
I knew Mr. Wu meant a lot to him,

21
00:03:26,479 --> 00:03:29,900
but I didn't expect that in matters of principle,

22
00:03:30,820 --> 00:03:34,140
he would actually defend a murderer.

23
00:03:36,020 --> 00:03:37,920
I don't understand.

24
00:03:40,460 --> 00:03:46,059
I'm surprised as well. Perhaps Jiang Chang Yang
is just protective of his loved ones.

25
00:03:46,059 --> 00:03:48,970
He had always treated us well,

26
00:03:48,970 --> 00:03:53,040
and over time, we forgot that he was the Floral Envoy,

27
00:03:53,040 --> 00:03:55,900
a corrupt official with a notorious reputation.

28
00:03:59,319 --> 00:04:04,299
I forgot. He is best at acting.

29
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:11,300
Let the past be the past.
Mr. Wu is also a pitiable person.

30
00:04:11,300 --> 00:04:16,120
Mu Dan, let it go.

31
00:04:16,120 --> 00:04:22,120
All these years, Mr. Wu has lived a frugal life.
He has been atoning for his sins.

32
00:04:22,120 --> 00:04:24,620
- Ms. He. 
 - Mr. Wu,

33
00:04:27,220 --> 00:04:29,079
no need to say anything.

34
00:04:32,360 --> 00:04:38,179
Not just Jiang Chang Yang,
why was Mr. Wu so calm when he saw me?

35
00:04:38,179 --> 00:04:41,419
As if he had already anticipated
that I would come to find him.

36
00:04:42,639 --> 00:04:48,419
And Mother, why did she never mention this to me?

37
00:04:49,600 --> 00:04:52,140
There is a big difference
between the symptoms of poisoning and disease.

38
00:04:52,140 --> 00:04:56,580
You must truthfully inform the doctor
to receive the right treatment.

39
00:04:57,759 --> 00:05:02,739
In past medical consultations,
Father and Mother always sent me away.

40
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:10,480
No, I must find out the truth.

41
00:05:10,480 --> 00:05:12,200
Mu Dan,

42
00:05:14,000 --> 00:05:15,940
I have checked everything you asked me to investigate.

43
00:05:15,940 --> 00:05:19,419
Since returning from Luoyang to Chang'an,
Mr. Wu has stayed at the orphanage infirmary.

44
00:05:19,419 --> 00:05:21,399
He only comes into contact with those children.

45
00:05:21,399 --> 00:05:24,620
He has no other friends or family around now.

46
00:05:38,979 --> 00:05:40,680
What are you writing?

47
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:44,720
This is the list of names and approximate ages
of all the children living in the orphanage.

48
00:05:44,720 --> 00:05:47,560
For a few, I only know their nicknames.

49
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:51,120
You'll need to ask the long-term residents
of the nearby village.

50
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:53,859
Why are you investigating these children?

51
00:05:53,859 --> 00:06:00,219
I want to know if any of these children
came from Luoyang.

52
00:06:03,519 --> 00:06:07,859
Kang. Kang.

53
00:06:09,399 --> 00:06:13,439
Kang usually comes here to play every day.
Why is he not here today?

54
00:06:18,260 --> 00:06:20,760
- Stop. You, stop.
- Are you Kang?

55
00:06:20,760 --> 00:06:23,199
- Where did you get hit? Does it hurt? 
 - I'm fine.

56
00:06:23,199 --> 00:06:24,959
- Let go of me.
- Come here.

57
00:06:24,959 --> 00:06:27,539
- Let go of me.
- He is Kang.

58
00:06:27,539 --> 00:06:29,700
What kind of hero attacks from behind?

59
00:06:29,700 --> 00:06:31,960
- Let go.
- Don't move.

60
00:06:32,720 --> 00:06:34,540
Stand here now.

61
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:38,200
- Give it back to me. 
 - No, I won't.

62
00:06:38,200 --> 00:06:40,439
Kang, I have a question.

63
00:06:40,439 --> 00:06:43,720
Usually, you're very well-behaved and polite.
Why did you hit me today?

64
00:06:43,720 --> 00:06:47,839
And you hit her so hard, despite the fact
that Mu Dan often sends you clothes and food.

65
00:06:47,839 --> 00:06:49,419
Heartless.

66
00:06:49,419 --> 00:06:50,739
You're a bad person.

67
00:06:50,739 --> 00:06:52,360
Don't send anything.
I don't want your stuff anymore.

68
00:06:52,360 --> 00:06:53,940
Let go. Let me go.

69
00:06:53,940 --> 00:06:56,060
Why do you say that?

70
00:06:58,179 --> 00:07:01,140
I saw you trying to harm Mr. Wu.

71
00:07:01,140 --> 00:07:03,739
You are a big villain.

72
00:07:03,739 --> 00:07:05,779
How do you know Mr. Wu is not the villain?

73
00:07:05,779 --> 00:07:10,480
Mr. Wu is a very good person. He saved my life.

74
00:07:12,419 --> 00:07:13,900
Slow down, slow down.

75
00:07:13,900 --> 00:07:16,779
You have a fever from tuberculosis. Speak slowly.

76
00:07:17,380 --> 00:07:19,280
Have some water, here.

77
00:07:20,460 --> 00:07:23,160
- What are you doing? 
 - I don't need your kindness.

78
00:07:23,160 --> 00:07:26,839
If it weren't for Mr. Wu,
I would have died in the flood that year.

79
00:07:26,839 --> 00:07:31,020
If you want to harm him, you are my enemy.

80
00:07:31,879 --> 00:07:36,539
Kang, are you talking about the flood disaster
in Luoyang four years ago?

81
00:07:36,539 --> 00:07:38,659
Are you really from Luoyang?

82
00:07:40,040 --> 00:07:42,519
I am.

83
00:07:42,519 --> 00:07:48,060
Back then, many people caught the plague,
and few in the village survived.

84
00:07:49,460 --> 00:07:56,979
My parents and my sister
couldn't survive, only I did.

85
00:07:57,920 --> 00:08:01,360
By that time, Mr. Wu's family had all passed away.

86
00:08:01,360 --> 00:08:05,020
He luckily got the medicine,
but it was already too late.

87
00:08:05,020 --> 00:08:09,060
By chance, he met me and gave me the medicine.

88
00:08:09,060 --> 00:08:11,539
That's how I was able to save my life.

89
00:08:15,680 --> 00:08:19,639
So many people died in that epidemic.

90
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:29,220
Kang, tell me, where did Mr. Wu find the medicine?

91
00:08:29,759 --> 00:08:33,179
Mr. Wu said he found it in a merchant's house.

92
00:08:33,179 --> 00:08:35,000
Was the merchant's surname He?

93
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:38,200
Mr. Wu didn't say, but it's definitely not.

94
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,779
Why are you so sure?

95
00:08:39,779 --> 00:08:42,860
Back then, the plague was not incurable.

96
00:08:42,860 --> 00:08:47,759
But the medicine was expensive
and required rare peony bark.

97
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:52,659
It's said that the He's pharmacy in the city
had such peony bark.

98
00:08:52,659 --> 00:08:56,000
But the pharmacy owner
took the opportunity to drive up the prices

99
00:08:56,000 --> 00:08:59,220
and sold all the peony bark to noble families.

100
00:09:03,440 --> 00:09:05,020
Could you be mistaken?

101
00:09:05,020 --> 00:09:08,179
I remember it very clearly.

102
00:09:08,179 --> 00:09:14,360
Back then, my parents, I, and the whole village
knelt outside the pharmacy for several days.

103
00:09:14,360 --> 00:09:18,120
But we were told
that all the peony bark was used up.

104
00:09:18,120 --> 00:09:22,179
But I clearly saw them carrying
medicinal packets onto the carriage.

105
00:09:22,179 --> 00:09:24,779
The packets were extremely beautiful.

106
00:09:27,879 --> 00:09:33,220
Tell me, what pattern was printed
on the medicinal packets?

107
00:09:33,220 --> 00:09:36,679
It was clouds, red clouds.

108
00:09:36,679 --> 00:09:41,020
I also hoped my parents
could have a pack of clouds.

109
00:09:42,239 --> 00:09:46,520
But even until they died kneeling
at the pharmacy's door, no one cared.

110
00:09:47,179 --> 00:09:51,519
The people in the village
also collapsed one by one.

111
00:09:52,599 --> 00:09:55,559
The open space in the back hill
could no longer accommodate.

112
00:09:55,559 --> 00:10:00,059
Too many people died, too many.

113
00:10:00,059 --> 00:10:04,389
Mr. Wu said that the peony owner
turned a blind eye to death,

114
00:10:04,389 --> 00:10:07,659
so the peony bark she had
was no different from poison.

115
00:10:07,659 --> 00:10:10,000
It wasn't a natural disaster that killed everyone.

116
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:13,340
The He family pharmacy
is the murderous demon and our enemy.

117
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:16,639
Don't talk nonsense, child. Don't talk nonsense.

118
00:10:16,639 --> 00:10:18,299
I'm not talking nonsense.

119
00:10:18,299 --> 00:10:20,099
Stop talking.

120
00:10:40,240 --> 00:10:47,859
Kang, after Mr. Wu saved you all those years ago,
why did you come to Chang'an?

121
00:10:48,539 --> 00:10:51,020
Big Brother brought us here.

122
00:10:51,020 --> 00:10:53,020
It was Jiang Chang Yang.

123
00:10:55,740 --> 00:10:58,299
Mr. Wu fed me the medicine.

124
00:10:58,299 --> 00:11:05,820
At night, I woke up groggy
and saw that he had hanged himself.

125
00:11:09,639 --> 00:11:10,639
Mr. Wu.

126
00:11:10,639 --> 00:11:13,220
Big Brother arrived in time and saved him.

127
00:11:13,220 --> 00:11:15,220
Sir.

128
00:11:17,000 --> 00:11:22,380
That night, Mr. Wu cried for a long time,
and Big Brother persuaded him for a long time.

129
00:11:22,380 --> 00:11:27,579
Big Brother told me that from then on,
I would be Mr. Wu's son.

130
00:11:27,579 --> 00:11:30,559
Only if the brothers and sisters
in the courtyard are safe and sound,

131
00:11:30,559 --> 00:11:33,320
can Mr. Wu live well.

132
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:50,360
The root and bark of this flower can clear heat,
cool the blood, and alleviate various pains.

133
00:11:50,360 --> 00:11:55,740
Combined with anemarrhena, phellodendron,
and rehmannia, it can relieve lung heat.

134
00:11:55,740 --> 00:11:59,020
It is exactly the medicine
most needed for this epidemic.

135
00:11:59,020 --> 00:12:04,819
The ice crystal peonies we have are the rarest
and hardest to find over vast distances.

136
00:12:04,819 --> 00:12:09,860
In these times of disaster,
one of these is worth a fortune.

137
00:12:11,140 --> 00:12:13,959
I grew up by my mother's side.

138
00:12:15,099 --> 00:12:18,160
I know her character very well.

139
00:12:18,160 --> 00:12:21,440
She is definitely not such a heartless person.

140
00:12:21,440 --> 00:12:24,720
Could there be any misunderstanding in this?

141
00:12:25,799 --> 00:12:27,620
My mother understands pharmacology.

142
00:12:27,620 --> 00:12:31,740
If someone poisoned her,
she would definitely notice.

143
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:35,870
But she never mentioned it until her last breath.

144
00:12:37,620 --> 00:12:40,200
So why would Auntie know about it?

145
00:12:45,919 --> 00:12:47,919
I need to return to Luoyang.

146
00:12:49,179 --> 00:12:50,979
Coming.

147
00:12:56,080 --> 00:12:58,779
What? Can't I enter this house anymore?

148
00:12:58,779 --> 00:13:00,720
Mu Dan, what are you doing?

149
00:13:00,720 --> 00:13:05,699
Wasn't our deal settled in Chang'an?
Are you going back on your word?

150
00:13:05,699 --> 00:13:07,559
I came to Luoyang to find my father.

151
00:13:07,559 --> 00:13:09,240
It has nothing to do with you, so step aside.

152
00:13:09,240 --> 00:13:12,579
If you have severed ties with the He family,
you should behave yourself.

153
00:13:12,579 --> 00:13:15,600
Please stop looking for the Master, will you?

154
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:17,300
Mu Dan?

155
00:13:21,419 --> 00:13:25,200
It really is you. Why didn't you
send a letter before coming home?

156
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:28,620
- That's… That's right.
- Hurry, come on in.

157
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:38,519
Why bring the past matter up now?

158
00:13:41,080 --> 00:13:45,380
You only told me that Mother suddenly fell ill.

159
00:13:46,279 --> 00:13:50,579
No one told me that it was due to poisoning.

160
00:13:51,919 --> 00:13:53,860
How could you think so, Mu Dan?
Your mother was not…

161
00:13:53,860 --> 00:13:57,759
Father, there's no need
to hide it anymore. I already know.

162
00:13:57,759 --> 00:13:59,519
It was Wu Hong's doing.

163
00:13:59,519 --> 00:14:01,119
How did you…

164
00:14:05,759 --> 00:14:12,000
When you said you were visiting home,
you actually went to Chang'an to see Mu Dan.

165
00:14:12,000 --> 00:14:14,620
Are you blaming me?

166
00:14:14,620 --> 00:14:18,279
Have you seen the house? We're almost emptied out.

167
00:14:18,279 --> 00:14:23,080
Since Mu Dan is a He family daughter,
what's wrong with helping the family?

168
00:14:23,080 --> 00:14:25,440
Why did you act on your own?

169
00:14:28,200 --> 00:14:32,699
Mu Dan, I didn't know
that it was your money and silk.

170
00:14:32,699 --> 00:14:37,600
In two years, within two years,
I will definitely pay you back.

171
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:40,679
Pay her back? Why would you?

172
00:14:40,679 --> 00:14:42,500
Shut up.

173
00:14:42,500 --> 00:14:46,679
As a He family daughter,
Mu Dan is obligated to support her parents.

174
00:14:46,679 --> 00:14:48,960
Moreover, she is now wealthy.

175
00:14:48,960 --> 00:14:50,919
You haven't seen it.

176
00:14:50,919 --> 00:14:54,340
She is thriving as a shop owner.

177
00:14:54,340 --> 00:14:57,960
Such a small amount of money
is hardly noticeable to her.

178
00:14:57,960 --> 00:15:00,259
- Shut your mouth.
- I…

179
00:15:11,559 --> 00:15:16,879
Father, I did not come today to ask for money.

180
00:15:16,879 --> 00:15:22,539
If Auntie didn't tell me, I couldn't find out
about what happened back then.

181
00:15:24,819 --> 00:15:26,759
How much have you found out?

182
00:15:26,759 --> 00:15:28,919
A lot.

183
00:15:28,919 --> 00:15:35,240
When the plague ravaged Luoyang back then,
Mother's ice crystal peonies could save lives.

184
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:42,259
Father, did you sell the peony bark
to high officials back then?

185
00:15:46,600 --> 00:15:49,440
I've been thinking on my way here.

186
00:15:49,440 --> 00:15:54,220
How could the parents I have admired
and loved since childhood

187
00:15:54,220 --> 00:15:59,380
be such greedy people
who ignore others' suffering?

188
00:15:59,380 --> 00:16:03,200
No, you cannot speak of your mother like that.

189
00:16:03,200 --> 00:16:06,360
She was not aware of this matter.

190
00:16:06,360 --> 00:16:08,399
What do you mean?

191
00:16:08,399 --> 00:16:12,360
I was the one who sold
the peony bark at a high price.

192
00:16:12,360 --> 00:16:16,360
Your mother did not know
the destination of those medicinal materials.

193
00:16:16,360 --> 00:16:21,960
I told her I distributed them
to the infected common people.

194
00:16:21,960 --> 00:16:24,060
Why?

195
00:16:24,060 --> 00:16:27,900
Was it just to make more money
amidst the natural disaster?

196
00:16:28,919 --> 00:16:33,720
At that time, the plague was fierce,
and high officials were all in panic.

197
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:39,200
They forced me to sell all the medicine to them.

198
00:16:39,799 --> 00:16:44,220
But after the flood that year,
the common people's water and food were polluted,

199
00:16:44,220 --> 00:16:46,340
which caused the epidemic.

200
00:16:46,340 --> 00:16:48,779
The nobles stayed in their houses all day,

201
00:16:48,779 --> 00:16:52,200
eating precious and clean food.

202
00:16:52,200 --> 00:16:54,679
How could they easily get sick?

203
00:16:54,679 --> 00:16:58,059
Those nobles didn't care about that.

204
00:16:58,059 --> 00:16:59,879
If one or two of their servants

205
00:16:59,879 --> 00:17:04,140
who went out to purchase goods fell ill,
they were terrified.

206
00:17:04,140 --> 00:17:08,799
They needed to have hundreds of doses
of medicine at home to feel at ease.

207
00:17:08,799 --> 00:17:14,920
Even though they were healthy,
they hoarded medicine and refused to save lives.

208
00:17:15,820 --> 00:17:20,499
Father, I can't believe you agreed to this deal.

209
00:17:20,499 --> 00:17:26,240
As a mere merchant, if I had angered the powerful,

210
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:30,599
they would have closed down all our shops.

211
00:17:30,599 --> 00:17:34,979
At that time, you and your mother
would also be implicated.

212
00:17:35,720 --> 00:17:40,259
Mu Dan, I didn't dare to take the risk.

213
00:17:41,559 --> 00:17:43,710
So at that time,

214
00:17:45,130 --> 00:17:47,270
you kept it from us.

215
00:17:48,279 --> 00:17:51,820
Your mother is kind and gentle,
only focused on flowers and plants.

216
00:17:51,820 --> 00:17:53,240
And you were young.

217
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:58,979
Telling you about this
would only add to your worries.

218
00:17:58,979 --> 00:18:05,839
I cannot bear to let you
and your mother suffer with me.

219
00:18:05,839 --> 00:18:07,680
So, Mother

220
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:12,580
later found out.

221
00:18:15,620 --> 00:18:18,219
Wu Hong told her.

222
00:18:18,720 --> 00:18:23,620
 After the calamity subsided, someone disguised
as a vegetable farmer sneaked into the house. 

223
00:18:23,620 --> 00:18:28,760
 Your mother sympathized with him
and gave him some food and money. 

224
00:18:29,519 --> 00:18:33,419
 That person was Wu Hong. 

225
00:18:34,880 --> 00:18:37,459
How did it come to this?

226
00:18:37,459 --> 00:18:41,319
If the medicine is taken on time,
recovery should come in a few days.

227
00:18:41,319 --> 00:18:45,780
This expensive medicine
can only be afforded by the wealthy.

228
00:18:45,780 --> 00:18:50,200
How can lowly people like us afford it?

229
00:18:50,200 --> 00:18:57,699
He's pharmacy's peony bark was free,
with no distinction between noble and common.

230
00:18:58,300 --> 00:18:59,950
Free?

231
00:18:59,950 --> 00:19:06,400
Madam, are you truly unaware
of the price of this medicine?

232
00:19:08,160 --> 00:19:14,240
Was my peony bark sold
at a high price to sick people?

233
00:19:14,240 --> 00:19:16,540
If it can be bought at a high price, it'd be fine.

234
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:20,359
Your medicine would not
be sold to ordinary people at all.

235
00:19:20,359 --> 00:19:23,659
Instead, it was delivered
to the mansions of high officials and nobles.

236
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,960
How could this be?

237
00:19:25,960 --> 00:19:30,599
This life-saving medicine is hard to obtain,
and it's a perfect opportunity to make a fortune.

238
00:19:30,599 --> 00:19:37,119
It seems that Storekeeper He
did not tell you the truth either.

239
00:19:39,519 --> 00:19:42,619
- Outside… 
 - Outside, corpses are scattered everywhere.

240
00:19:42,619 --> 00:19:47,960
Half a month ago, people were indeed
kneeling in front of He's Pharmacy.

241
00:19:47,960 --> 00:19:51,640
From dawn till dusk, they kowtowed continuously,
only asking for a packet of medicine.

242
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:57,160
But now those who sought medicine
have long passed away.

243
00:19:57,160 --> 00:20:03,359
Among those unjust spirits are my whole family.

244
00:20:10,279 --> 00:20:15,240
In the past half month,
I wandered around the mansions of the nobles.

245
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:17,960
Yet no one paid any attention to me.

246
00:20:17,960 --> 00:20:22,440
If Storekeeper He were home today,
he would probably drive me away, too.

247
00:20:22,440 --> 00:20:28,319
By a twist of fate, I happened to encounter you.

248
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:51,880
I poisoned the tea, Madam.
Report it to the authorities.

249
00:20:51,880 --> 00:20:55,799
Whether to kill or flay, I am at your disposal.

250
00:20:55,799 --> 00:20:58,469
Fate plays tricks.

251
00:20:58,469 --> 00:21:01,540
I wanted to avenge my family,

252
00:21:01,540 --> 00:21:08,179
but little did I know that as the source
of the medicine, you were unaware of this.

253
00:21:11,960 --> 00:21:16,200
You don't need to find someone
to capture me. I will not run.

254
00:21:16,200 --> 00:21:22,000
Now I am all alone
and have no intention of clinging to life.

255
00:21:35,580 --> 00:21:40,540
This is the last bit
of the ice crystal peony root bark.

256
00:21:41,799 --> 00:21:47,200
I'm not sure if anyone
still needs it at this moment.

257
00:21:48,939 --> 00:21:51,179
Madam, what are you doing?

258
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,900
You should leave.

259
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:02,599
Aren't you going to report it to the authorities?

